com.wizturn.sdk

Class PeripheralChangeEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wizturn.sdk.PeripheralChangeEvent

  • public class PeripheralChangeEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines characteristic change events of Peripheral. In order to create an instance of PeripheralChangeEvent, you should use the the following methods.
    PeripheralChageEvent#createEvent(int), createEvent(int, String)

    For an example of using this method, refer to the following inline code.
    PeripheralChangeEvent event = PeripheralChangeEvent.createEvent( PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_TX_POWER);
    Creating an instance of it is not necessary mostly. For each event, process flow should be different by writing codes like below. 

     final int changeEvent = event.getEvent();
 switch(changeEvent) {
     case PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_ADVERTISEMENT_INTERVAL:
         // TODO do something
         break;
     case PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_MAJOR:
         // TODO do something
         break;
     case PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_MINOR:
         // TODO do something
         break;
     case PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_PROXIMITY_UUID:
         // TODO do something
         break;
     case PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_TX_POWER:
         // TODO do something
         break;
     case PeripheralChangeEvent.CHANGE_UNKNWON:
         // TODO do something, errors occur. Plz, handle.
         break;
 }
